# Notion Tasks

**Full guide:** `docs/notion.md` § Task anchor in chat · Execute: `@notion-execute-task`

## Task anchor (mandatory while working on TODO)

1. Set `NOTION_TASK_URL` from user link or `notion-fetch` — **before any file edits**
2. **Every reply** starts with: `**Notion:** [title](URL) · **Status:** …`
3. **Every code pass** (incl. small fixes):
   - Start → `In progress` + `notion-create-comment`
   - End → comment summary + `Review`
4. **Subagent prompt** must include `NOTION_TASK_URL`, `NOTION_TASK_PAGE_ID`, `ITERATION`
5. Subagent first/last message echoes the Notion link

## Create task

`docs/notion-create-task.md` or `@notion-create-task` — do not implement.

## Execute task

In progress → **Review** each pass → **Done** only after user says commit.

**Never:** edit files without anchored URL · skip comments · skip status update

## Ship (commit — any chat)

`@notion-ship-task` / `haku-notion-ship.mdc` — resolve task URL → commit → comment → **Done**.

## MCP

`plugin-notion-workspace-notion` · Auth fail → `mcp_auth`
